# JavaScript Class Structure

```javascript
// Define a class
class Animal {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
  }

  speak() {
    console.log(`${this.name} makes a sound`);
  }
}

// Create an instance
const a = new Animal('Dog');
a.speak(); // Output: Dog makes a sound
```

